-- This is a CA Compliant 995 which means it has a "bullet button" that you'll need a tool to pop the magazine out with, and also that you won't be able to buy one after Jan 1, 2017 -- so get it while you can.  This is a great little gun -- pretty accurate, fun to shoot, and has always been reliable for me.  Already has a front grip so you're halfway there to mounting a light or a laser on the front rail, which Hi-Point makes for cheap (see yellow accessory list in pic).  Hi-Point's also have a lifetime warranty.  Reason for selling is that I don't feel like registering this as an "assault weapon," and I might put the money into an actual AR platform if I want to be on the list.
